  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver employs tunable configuration parameters including base mesh element size (0.15 mm near-wall), hemolysis scalar transport threshold (1e-5), and iterative convergence tolerance (1e-4 for momentum residuals). Validation results are reported at the chosen settings; however, these values are described only in narrative and are not captured in any structured configuration node linked to this package. The ContextOfUse does not constrain or specify deployment configuration, leaving open the possibility that production runs use different settings than those present during validation.",
