      "name": "Hemolysis index benchmark against FDA experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against FDA GCBP experimental measurements at five flow-speed operating points. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 satisfied at all operating points at the chosen solver settings. Mesh element size of 0.15 mm in near-wall regions, convergence tolerance 1e-4, and hemolysis threshold 1e-5 were used during this validation exercise. These parameter values are documented in the analyst's run log but are not formally pinned in any structured configuration record linked to this assurance package."
