      "name": "Mesh sensitivity and discretization error assessment",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed using element sizes of 0.30 mm, 0.15 mm, and 0.075 mm. Richardson extrapolation applied; GCI < 3% for NIH quantity of interest on the medium mesh selected for production runs. Results reported at the chosen mesh configuration; no structured field binds the selected mesh size to this package for deployment verification."
    },
