    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. The CFD model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 satisfied at all five operating points. The assessment team notes that configuration parameters (mesh element size 0.15 mm, convergence tolerance 1e-4, hemolysis threshold 1e-5) are documented in analyst run logs and validation narratives; however, these values have not been captured in a structured configuration binding within this assurance package and the ContextOfUse does not formally constrain deployment configuration. This gap is acknowledged but not considered disqualifying at MRL 2. Regulatory submission may proceed subject to deployment team confirming use of validated configuration settings.",
